BTW pointing out design flaws or some legitimate pvp strategies as I did above isn't meaning to say rogues suck they don't. As far as your friend there well guess what an awesome pvper is probably going to rock no matter what class he or she plays but that doesn't mean that rogues as a class should have to deal with every gimp caster using what is to me an obviously exploitive strategy.<br>
<br>
I pointed out a few strategies that don't require you to be &quot;too close&quot; to a melee unless too close is anywhere they can see you and attack you back lol which personally is what I think your saying.<br>
<br>
Considering the feedback I would be quite happy if the following changes were made...<br>
<br>
-Line of sight required on all nukes debuffs and dots.<br>
-Charm no longer poofed pets.<br>
-Pumice casting time was lowered somewhat or a new pumice was added that doesn't proc till 50 with a lower casting time.  If you did this you could dispose of golem wands they are kinda unbalancing in some cases.<br>
-The pet attack assist trick was nerfed and /invite playername was a command usable zone wide to make Coth possible.<br>
-Ghosting was adressed in some fashion<br>
-The position of a player you have targeted relative to you should be calculated more precisely and checked more often so that players could hit eachother more easily with melee attacks.<br>
<br>
<br>
Requests removed for shaman ds and levitate changes.<br>
<br>
I think that all of these requests would lead to more interesting and more balanced gameplay. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/25/01 7:26:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=518.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Broken or poorly designed aspects and strategies in pvp</span><hr size=1> Forgot to adress this bs here.<br>
